    "id": "gdmrp-0005",
    "correctOption": "C",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "sourceYear": 2024,
    "en": {
      "question": "A bag contains Rs. 216 in the form of one-rupee, 50-paise, and 25-paise coins in the ratio 2 : 3 : 4. How many 50-paise coins are there?",
      "options": [
        "72",
        "96",
        "144",
        "168"
      ],
      "explanation": "Value ratio: 2x1 : 3x0.5 : 4x0.25 = 2 : 1.5 : 1 = 4 : 3 : 2. Sum = 9 parts. Value of 50p coins = 3/9 x 216 = 72. Number = 72/0.5 = 144."
    },
    "hi": {
      "question": "एक थैले में Rs. 216, एक रुपये, 50 पैसे और 25 पैसे के सिक्कों के रूप में 2 : 3 : 4 के अनुपात में हैं। 50 पैसे के कितने सिक्के हैं?",
      "options": [
        "72",
        "96",
        "144",
        "168"
      ],
      "explanation": "मूल्य अनुपात: 2×1 : 3×0.5 : 4×0.25 = 2 : 1.5 : 1 = 4 : 3 : 2। योग = 9 भाग। 50 पैसे के सिक्कों का मूल्य = 3/9 × 216 = 72। संख्या = 72/0.5 = 144।"
    }
  },
